:<div>

bark /bɑːk/

(barking,barked,barks) 

1. V-I When a dog barks , it makes a short, loud noise, once or several times. (狗) 吠 

例： Don't let the dogs bark. 别让狗叫。 

2. N-COUNT Bark is also a noun. 吠声 

例： The Doberman let out a string of roaring barks. 那条杜宾犬发出一连串的吼叫声。 

3. V-I If you bark at someone, you shout at them aggressively in a loud, rough voice. 咆哮 

例： I didn't mean to bark at you. 我不是有意吼你。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Bark is the tough material that covers the outside of a tree. 树皮 

5. V to scrape or rub off skin, as in an injury 擦伤; 刮伤

